array.note: s[i] is the city succeeding to the ith city (itself if not part of the route)
d[i] is the distance (seen as a travel cost) between the ith city and its successor
l[i] is the purchase location of the ith product (last city has nothing for sale)
c[i] is the purchase cost of the ith product

block.note: linking purchase locations to purchase costs

group.note: purchasing a product at a city is only possible if you visit that city

intension.note: last city must be visited (we start here)
